1. In the below elements which of them are values or an expression? eg:- values can be
integer or string and expressions will be mathematical operators

Ans->  In the following elements the values are 'hello', -87.8, 6 and Expressions are *, -, /, +

2. What is the difference between string and variable?

Ans-> String is a data type, a sequence of characters. In python a string is represented with single or double quotes. Whereas a variable is a naem that holds / refers any values. 
It can be of any data type such as int, float, boolean, string etc

3. Describe three different data types

Ans->
Int - Integer data type contains a whole number(non floating value). It can be negative or positive whole number. Eg -> 50, -23, 1, 5
Float - Float data type contains franctions(numbers with decimals). Eg-> 2.365, 50.21, 12.0
String - String data type contains sequence of characters. It can be represented with '' or "". Eg -> "Data Analytics", 'Hello World', '99999'

4. What is an expression made up of? What do all expressions do?

Ans-> An expression can be made up off variables, values and operators. It produces some result after being interpreted

5. This assignment statements, like spam = 10. What is the difference between an
expression and a statement?

Ans-> An expression evaluates to a value, whereas a statement performs an action. In the assignment statement "spam = 10", "spam" is a variable, and "10" is a value. 
The entire statement is an example of a statement because it assigns the value 10 to the variable spam

6. After running the following code, what does the variable bacon contain?
bacon = 22
bacon + 1

Ans-> the value 22 is stored in variable bacon. next, when 1 is added to it the value becomes 23 but will not change the original value 22 which is stored in bacon variable. 


